Description: Two non-joining sherds of pottery open vessel, perhaps Corinthian. Both glazed on inside; one plain on outside, the other (f) has part of the neck of a swan or goose with added red dot.
Curator's comments: Sherds presumably rejected from rebuilding of 1886,0401.1098a-e.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GS.330)
